      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROCKNROLL WILLOW (10) scored by 6 metres at Stawell over 1785m last start at her first run back from a spell. Draws out a little on the second line and may need luck at some point. Finds a tougher race but another win is not out of the question. BACKBEACH PETER (3) settled handy the went to the front and closed the race off well to win for the second time in a row last start over 1780m at Mt Gambier, getting there by 13 metres. No excuses from this advantageous draw. Taking on a better line-up this time but he has the ability to mix it with them. STEAM MACHINE (9) is next in line and although he has to contend with an awkward gate a win is not out of the question. LUCKY VINCENT (1) disappointed last time when ninth over 2240m at Melton. Can make amends.",
